node.text:
YAY or NAY? Here's the longer version for making homemade chocolate 🍫🤩

Even though it’s a lengthy process, I loved learning how to make chocolate from cocoa beans. The freshly roasted cacao beans smell just so heavenly. 🍫

I’ve explained how to make chocolate in lots of details on my blog, check this post:
https://www.alphafoodie.com/how-to-make-chocolate-bean-to-bar/

Do you like chocolate?
Credit: @alphafoodie #foodguidelines

node.text:
Follow @mealplans for food fact that will blow your mind @mealplans 

Drinking green tea before bed ?

Green tea is not a drink before bedtime if the caffeine can disturb your sleep. It contains the amino acid of L-Theanine which makes you awake and concentrate better. The best time to drink is two hours before bedtime or after a meal because this is the lowest metabolism moment and the green tea can increase it. You can drink 2-3 cups in a day.

Made by @healthyfoodadvice . .

node.text:
Who loves fancy bread meals!?..This could be lunch for breakfast! 😋

Pick your fav by @toastedtable …1,2,3,4,5 or 6?

Toast 1- whole grain, smashed avocado 🥑, goat cheese, local cherry tomatoes, mint + dill, chili-flakes & @mikeshothoney 🔥

Toast 2- Whole grain loaf, smashed 🥑, smashed hard-boiled eggs, olives, mint, sesame & aleppo pepper 🤪

Toast 3- Sprouted bread, smashed 🥑, sliced peaches, seared halloumi, sesame + nigella seeds, honey 🍯

Toast 4- Sprouted bread, smashed 🥑 avocado, ricotta whipped with preserved lemon 🍋+cinnamon + honey, fresh black figs, dill, cracked black pepper & extra honey 🍯

Toast 5- seeded bread, smashed 🥑 avocado, miso-ginger glazed salmon, extra sesame seeds + cilantro ☺️

Toast 6- a little bagel-inspired, homemade seeded bread, smashed 🥑 avocado, labneh, everything but the bagel smoked salmon, extra everything bagel seasoning, dill & cilantro 😋. 

#foodguidelines #food #healthy #yummy

node.text:
YAY or NAY? Roasted beet salad 🥗

This beetroot salad combines peppery arugula with earthy sweet beetroot, creamy goat cheese (optional), and crunchy walnuts with a tangy homemade honey mustard dressing! I simply love making it in the summer - so fresh! 🤩

Check out all the details and lots of tips on my blog, here’s the link:
https://www.alphafoodie.com/roasted-beet-salad-with-goat-cheese/ (link in bio)
Credit: @alphafoodie #foodguidelines
Do you like beetroot? Would you try this salad? ☺️

node.text:
Smashed potato X batata harra 🌶 🥔 and it honestly doesn’t get any better than this. By @nutrientmatters
I love this combo because traditionally batata harra is fried so it’s nice and crispy but with smashed potatoes, you get a baked crispy potato on the outside and fluffy, creamy goodness on the inside 🤤 
.
Ingredients:
1 lb yellow baby potatoes 
2 tbsp avocado 
1/2 tsp paprika 
1/4 tsp garlic powder 
1/4 tsp sea salt 
1/4 tsp black pepper 
.
2 tbsp butter unsalted 
2 garlic cloves minced 
1 tsp red pepper flakes 
2 tbsp fresh cilantro 
1 tsp lemon juice 
1 tsp lemon zest 
1-2 tbsp olive oil 
.
Bake potatoes for 45 mins at 405 degrees f. Brush with the spicy cilantro oil and bake for another 10 mins or until crisp. 
.
.
.
#potatoes #spicypotatoes #batataharra #middleeasternfood #feedfeed

I love making this quick and easy moutabal. One of my favorite ingredients is eggplant 🍆 (aubergine) and it’s simply delicious when made like this. Moutabal is perfect for eating with pita bread and enjoying with other mezze platters.
All the details for this recipe are on my blog, check this link:

node.text:
Spicy Salmon Bowls 👌🏻Now, I'm aware this is not traditional with the serrano and how I cut the fish, it’s an options and wanted to share with you 👌🏻by @foodmymuse

Ingredients:
•8 oz Sushi Grade Salmon (I buy mine at AJ's).
•1/4 cup Japanese mayo (kewpie).
•2-3 tbsp sriracha.
•1 tsp sesame oil.
•2 tsp soy sauce (I used shoyu).
•1 serrano pepper (optional and minced, adjust if you want it less hot).
•2 tbsp scallions.
•1/4 tsp cane sugar (optional but recommended).
•Sushi rice (I buy mine from my sushi place because he does it so much better than me).
•cucumber, avocado, nori strips, lemon and scallions for topping.

Directions:
1.- Cut up your fish in small cubes, typically for spicy rolls they mince it pretty small but I like mine with a bit of a bite. Smaller than poke but larger than usual spicy rolls if they makes sense.
2.- mix everything for the sauce. Add in the fish.
3.- serve over the rice and add toppings. #foodguidelines #food
